line_1: Or all his faults in blackest notes translate
line_2: To tombs where rot the authors of his fate;

line_1: To language all her looks translate,
line_2: And in her gestures read my fate.
This Dryden saw, and with his wonted fate

line_1: You best know how, — which way? — translate.
All these, my modest Satire bid translate,
line_2: And own'd, that nine such Poets made a Tate.

line_1: Thy poet's musing fancy would translate
line_2: Thus to the list'ning night to sing thy fate?
